The paper focuses on improving the evaluation speed of deep neural networks in retrieval scenarios, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) fields. The proposed approach involves a novel cascade of deep classifiers, which is trained end-to-end using a joint loss, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions applications such as object detection and image retrieval, which are commonly studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) fields.
